This paper deals with Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs) in cooperative multi-agent systems, which are typically studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and multi-agent systems (MA). The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving Functional DCOPs, which involves continuous non-linear optimization methods, making it likely to be categorized under machine learning (LG) and control systems (SY). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and algorithms suggests that it could also be categorized under robotics (RO).
